tag.inscription: This Red Oak was planted in 1991 to celebrate the Tercentenary of High Pavement Unitarian Chapel

Planted by H.E. Dr. L.M. Singvhu High Commissioner for  India in the Presence of Lord Mayor of Nottingham Councillor Vernon Gapper.  To symbolise Indo-British Friendship and to Commemorate the 125th Anniversary of Mahatma Gandhi.  31st October 1994
